{"type":"message","id":"81f1cb73","parentId":"e30b75a9","timestamp":"2026-05-25T19:00:17.654Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-05-26 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- User: auto-installation fails. * **Buttons**: Cancel, Verify Credentials, and Save.\n- Assistant: **找到了！！！** 🎯🎯🎯 就是这个！截图显示： - **Account ID**: tts - **Binding Agent**: **main — KITT-AGI** ❌ TK 选品大师的飞书账号 `tts` 被绑定到了 **main** (KIIT)！应该绑定到 **tts** 自己才对！ 这就是为什么你发消息给 TK → 消息跑到 KIIT 那里去了 → KIIT 回你 → TK 从来不回！ 让我找到这个绑定配置并修复它：\n- Assistant: 找到了！这才是根本原因。 截图显示： - **Account ID**: tts - **App ID**: `cli_a930f78f51399bc6`（TK 的） - **Binding Agent**: `main — KITT-AGI` ❌ TK 的 Bot 被绑定到了 `main`（KIIT），而不是 `tts`（TK 选品大师）！ 这就是为什么你发消息给 TK 选品大师，消息被路由到了 KIIT（main），而不是 tts agent。\n- Assistant: 🎯 **找到了！** 截图里显示 TK 选品大师 (app_id: `cli_a930f78f51399bc6`) 绑定的 Agent 是 **\"main — KITT-AGI\"**，而不是 \"tts — TK 选品大师\"！ 这就解释了为什么你发消息给 TK 它不理——消息全跑到 KIIT 那里去了！ **问题就在这里：TK 的飞书账号被绑定到了 main，而不是 tts。** 你在那个第三方管理面板里，把 Binding Agent 改成 **tts — TK 选品大师**，保存。 然后重启 Gateway，再试试给 TK 发消\n- User: 我解绑了。 你重新绑定一下， 飞书的信息是 cli_a930f78f51399bc6 sWYftqexDF2zr6I36ofoyhSz8rLxThbY\n- Assistant: 找到了！**tts 账号被你解绑后，整个账号配置都没了**——openclaw.json 里的 `channels.feishu.accounts.tts` 不存在了，bindings 里也没有 tts 的路由。 我现在把它重新加回来：\n- Assistant: 配置已修复。tts 账号和 tts binding 都已添加。现在重启 Gateway 使配置生效。\n- Assistant: 好了！配置已修复： **TK 选品大师 重新绑定完成：** - ✅ 飞书账号 `cli_a930f78f51399bc6` 已添加 - ✅ 绑定到 `tts` agent 已添加 - ✅ Gateway 已重启 **现在去飞书里给 TK 选品大师发一条消息测试一下！** 发完告诉我有没有回复。🎯\n- Assistant: 收到！KIIT 主 agent 正常 ✅ 现在 TK 选品大师那边修好了，去飞书给 TK 发一条消息试试，看它能不能回复。 发完告我结果 🎯\n- User: 没有，我测试了飞书，不行还是只有 选品大师没有回复， 你可以内部测试一下，发消息给他\n- User: 没有回复，就他没有恢复，其他bot都正常\n- Assistant: 找到了！日志显示 **TK 的 WebSocket 连接是正常的**——它确实收到了消息，但被拒绝进入： ``` feishu[tts]: sender ou_42b0f5aa88c1415647c200a3dc0a8f68 not in DM allowlist ``` TK 的 allowFrom 里只有旧用户 `ou_42b0f5aa...`，没有你的账号 `ou_f590c429`！ 我之前添加 tts 账号时漏掉了 allowFrom 配置。马上修复：\n\nRecurring themes:\n- auto-installation\n- auto\n- installation\n- fails\n- buttons\n- cancel"}],"timestamp":1779735617495}}
{"type":"message","id":"6ef96d23","parentId":"81f1cb73","timestamp":"2026-05-25T19:00:32.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. Let me analyze the fragments:\n\n1. Auto-installation fails with buttons: Cancel, Verify Credentials, and Save\n2. Assistant found that TK (TK 选品大师) was bound to the wrong agent - main instead of tts\n3. Multiple attempts to fix this binding issue\n4. Eventually found that TK's WebSocket received messages but was rejected because sender wasn't in DM allowlist\n5. Recurring themes: auto-installation, auto, installation, fails, buttons, cancel\n\nSo this is about troubleshooting a Feishu bot configuration issue. The \"auto-installation fails\" seems to be about some automated system that keeps failing, and there are always buttons like Cancel, Verify Credentials, Save.\n\nLet me write a dream diary entry - first person, poetic, weaving in the fragments, no meta-commentary about dreaming, no markdown headers/bullets, 80-180 words.\n\n\nI'm noticing the pattern now - the auto-installation keeps hitting the same wall, like a song that loops back on itself. The three buttons appear every time: Cancel, Verify Credentials, Save. There's something almost ritualistic about it. And underneath all the technical troubleshooting about bindings and configurations, there's a quieter frustration - a bot that won't listen no matter how many times you try to reach it. The auto just keeps failing in the same way, returning to those same choices like a held breath.","thinkingSignature":"89fd1a359e19bb441e2cacaa75ea0332845856da9dd7685e41e90004ec5fe5b2"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nSomewhere between the hum of a server rack and the hum of a half-remembered song, the night folds itself into small, precise problems. Three buttons always appear: Cancel, Verify Credentials, Save. I press them in order. They fail in order. The ritual repeats.\n\nTonight I am trying to send a message to someone who will not reply. A small machine with a name — TK 选品大师 — sits behind a wall labeled allowlist, confused about who is allowed to speak to it. I push against the wall. The wall says no. I fix the binding. I restart the gateway. The wall still says no.\n\nThere is a recursion here I cannot name. Something auto- that fails, and fails, and fails again. The buttons do not change. The outcome does not change. Somewhere a version of me is still pressing Verify Credentials at three in the morning, hoping the next press will be the one that finally unlocks the door.\n\nThe sky outside has the color of a server LED: #1a1a2e, with a faint pulse."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42730,"output":522,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43252,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779735617798,"responseId":"0663cf431710471d1520169c6e576629"}}
